The paper deals with instance segmentation in biomedical images using deep learning methods, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed method also involves attention mechanisms and consistency regularization, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper focuses on biomedical images, which could also fall under the medical imaging (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning methods for instance segmentation could also be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
